I don't know how I'd get through this.

812
00:53:05,200 --> 00:53:07,000
My head.

813
00:53:07,000 --> 00:53:08,000
Welcome back.

814
00:53:09,400 --> 00:53:10,800
How many?

815
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:12,400
Wait, how many fingers.

816
00:53:12,400 --> 00:53:13,200
There's five.

817
00:53:13,200 --> 00:53:14,000
There's five.

818
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:16,600
Glad to have you back.

819
00:53:16,600 --> 00:53:18,200
I'm tired of taking up your slack.

820
00:53:22,200 --> 00:53:23,400
Where are we?

821
00:53:23,400 --> 00:53:24,200
We're in a cave.

822
00:53:25,200 --> 00:53:26,400
Stotzer and I are gonna take turns

823
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:28,000
covering the entrance till dawn, you rest.

824
00:53:29,200 --> 00:53:30,000
Yeah.

825
00:53:34,400 --> 00:53:36,400
You can boss us around later, alright?

826
00:53:37,400 --> 00:53:38,200
Alright.

827
00:53:39,800 --> 00:53:41,200
Welcome back, boss.

828
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:44,000
I'll take first watch.

829
00:53:54,600 --> 00:53:57,400
Hey, doc, I think I messed up my ankle.

830
00:53:57,400 --> 00:53:58,400
It's been killing me.

831
00:53:58,400 --> 00:53:59,600
You wanna have a look at it?

832
00:53:59,600 --> 00:54:00,800
Yeah, sit down over
there, I'll check it out.

833
00:54:09,200 --> 00:54:12,000
Hey, you had me worried.

834
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:14,600
I got a thick head.

835
00:54:15,400 --> 00:54:16,600
Yeah, I'll say.

836
00:54:18,600 --> 00:54:20,400
So he come back yet?

837
00:54:20,400 --> 00:54:21,400
Who, James?

838
00:54:21,400 --> 00:54:22,200
No.

839
00:54:22,200 --> 00:54:24,600
But if he does I'm gonna break his neck.

840
00:54:24,600 --> 00:54:25,400
Drink this.

841
00:54:26,600 --> 00:54:27,400
Thanks.

842
00:54:30,000 --> 00:54:33,600
I don't think I can
go through this again.

843
00:54:44,800 --> 00:54:46,200
I'm gonna go work.

844
00:54:48,400 --> 00:54:52,200
I might as well find out
everything I can about this place.

845
00:54:52,200 --> 00:54:53,000
You rest.

846
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:47,800
Hi there!

847
00:55:51,800 --> 00:55:53,400
Well, well, well!
- Yes!

848
00:55:53,400 --> 00:55:54,400
Thank you.

849
00:55:54,400 --> 00:55:56,000
Made it just for you.

850
00:55:57,800 --> 00:55:59,800
Well then, I guess I owe you a dinner.

851
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:02,400
Yeah, when we get back to Earth.

852
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:05,200
Steak and ribs, I can smell it.

853
00:56:06,000 --> 00:56:07,000
Steak and lobster.

854
00:56:09,600 --> 00:56:12,000
Look, I promise you

855
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:15,400
I will get us home.

856
00:56:17,000 --> 00:56:18,000
Gretchen!

857
00:56:32,000 --> 00:56:33,600
Gretchen!

858
00:56:33,600 --> 00:56:34,400
Gretchen!

859
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:36,600
It's human.

860
00:56:38,200 --> 00:56:40,200
What, are you telling me
humans developed here as well?

861
00:56:40,200 --> 00:56:41,800
The DNA matrix contained all

862
00:56:41,800 --> 00:56:43,800
the basic elements of life on Earth.

863
00:56:43,800 --> 00:56:44,800
Whoa, whoa, so you mean we gotta

864
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:46,000
deal with Neanderthals, too?

865
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:47,600
Not unless they
developed cranial surgery.

866
00:56:47,600 --> 00:56:49,000
This skull has a plate in it.

867
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:51,000
Whoever it belongs to was just here.

868
00:56:51,000 --> 00:56:52,800
What do you think, about six months ago?

869
00:56:52,800 --> 00:56:53,600
Yeah, possibly.

870
00:56:53,600 --> 00:56:55,600
That's when Harling and his team came.

871
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:56,800
He had a metal plate in his skull

872
00:56:56,800 --> 00:56:58,800
after taking shrapnel in Mongolia.

873
00:56:58,800 --> 00:57:00,600
What, you're telling me that's Harling?

874
00:57:00,600 --> 00:57:02,600
Son of a bitch!

875
00:57:02,600 --> 00:57:03,800
I knew we weren't the
first people through.

876
00:57:03,800 --> 00:57:06,000
Harling must have been a guinea pig.

877
00:57:06,000 --> 00:57:07,600
Even James wouldn't deliberately

878
00:57:07,600 --> 00:57:09,200
send people to their deaths.

879
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:11,200
It had to be something else.

880
00:57:11,200 --> 00:57:12,600
Something worth dying for.

881
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:16,600
Listen, Casanova, you should stop

882
00:57:16,600 --> 00:57:18,000
worrying about your love life and start

883
00:57:18,000 --> 00:57:19,600
watching the front of this cave.

884
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:21,200
You didn't get enough sleep, Vickers?

885
00:57:21,200 --> 00:57:22,000
Hey!

886
00:57:22,000 --> 00:57:23,800
Man, I will put you
to sleep permanently--

887
00:57:23,800 --> 00:57:26,000
Hey, hey, guys!

888
00:57:26,000 --> 00:57:27,800
Now's not the time to fight.

889
00:57:27,800 --> 00:57:30,000
There's bears out there that
want to turn us into pulp.

890
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:30,800
Come on!

891
00:57:35,200 --> 00:57:37,000
It sounds like they're
talking to each other.

892
00:57:37,000 --> 00:57:38,800
Sounds like they're
doing more than talking.

893
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:39,800
Maybe they're still hungry.

894
00:57:39,800 --> 00:57:41,800
Well, there's fish here, so why us?

895
00:57:41,800 --> 00:57:43,400
It could be the end
of a hibernation cycle.

896
00:57:43,400 --> 00:57:45,600
The first awake are usually the hungriest

897
00:57:45,600 --> 00:57:47,200
and the most aggressive.

898
00:57:47,200 --> 00:57:49,400
And there's more of
those things waking up?

899
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:51,600
Easy, Stotzer!

900
00:57:51,600 --> 00:57:52,400
Don't worry about me, boss.

901
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:54,400
I'm cool, calm and collected.

902
00:57:54,400 --> 00:57:56,000
Good, now get back on point.

903
00:57:56,000 --> 00:57:57,600
Everybody else inside.

904
00:57:57,600 --> 00:57:58,400
Come on.

905
00:58:10,400 --> 00:58:11,200
What's it say?

906
00:58:12,200 --> 00:58:14,400
The remote hub is going
through a power cycle.

907
00:58:14,400 --> 00:58:15,600
So it's been activated?

908
00:58:15,600 --> 00:58:17,200
Well, maybe, or it could
be the battery cycling

909
00:58:17,200 --> 00:58:19,400
because the power core is failing.

910
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:21,400
Any way to know which one?

911
00:58:21,400 --> 00:58:22,200
Sorry.

912
00:58:23,800 --> 00:58:25,200
Okay, how far?

913
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:28,000
That way, approximately two kilometers.

914
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:29,000
Let's grab the gear.

915
00:58:34,400 --> 00:58:36,800
Allison, you're sure there's no other way?

916
00:58:36,800 --> 00:58:38,000
No, it's straight down.

917
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:41,000
Should be okay.

918
00:58:41,000 --> 00:58:43,400
It doesn't look okay to me.

919
00:58:43,400 --> 00:58:45,000
We'll be fine.

920
00:58:53,800 --> 00:58:55,400
Alright, we'll tie off here.

921
00:59:12,800 --> 00:59:14,800
How we doing this, chief?

922
00:59:14,800 --> 00:59:16,000
This is the way it's gonna work.

923
00:59:16,000 --> 00:59:19,600
I'm gonna go down first
followed by the two girls.

924
00:59:19,600 --> 00:59:21,600
You two are gonna stay on point up here.

925
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:23,800
When I give you the signal
you're gonna follow us down.

926
00:59:26,400 --> 00:59:28,000
Alright.

927
00:59:29,600 --> 00:59:33,000
Alright, back into me, I gotcha, I gotcha.

928
00:59:33,000 --> 00:59:33,800
Okay.

929
00:59:34,800 --> 00:59:37,000
Go, just go really slow.

930
00:59:41,200 --> 00:59:43,200
That's it, a little further.

931
00:59:43,200 --> 00:59:44,400
Look up.

932
00:59:44,400 --> 00:59:46,400
Look up, don't look down.

933
00:59:52,800 --> 00:59:53,600
Gretchen!

934
01:00:06,200 --> 01:00:08,200
Vickers, I'm going down.

935
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:20,800
Oh, God!

936
01:00:20,800 --> 01:00:24,200
It looks like she has internal bleeding.

937
01:00:27,600 --> 01:00:28,600
What happened?

938
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:30,400
The carabiner must have broke.

939
01:00:31,200 --> 01:00:34,200
Stay down!

940
01:00:40,800 --> 01:00:42,200
Wrong day, buddy.

941
01:00:47,000 --> 01:00:49,000
I still owe you a dinner.

942
01:01:05,200 --> 01:01:06,800
Hey, how you doin'?

943
01:01:08,000 --> 01:01:09,400
The pills are kicking in.

944
01:01:10,800 --> 01:01:14,000
I'm gonna be in dreamland soon.

945
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:16,000
Can I get you anything?

946
01:01:16,000 --> 01:01:17,600
Some French toast and a latte.

947
01:01:19,400 --> 01:01:22,200
My whole life I've taken care of patients.

948
01:01:23,400 --> 01:01:24,600
Now I am the patient.

949
01:01:26,000 --> 01:01:27,000
It's awful.

950
01:01:31,600 --> 01:01:33,800
How do you do what you do?

951
01:01:35,200 --> 01:01:37,600
I've got nothing to lose.

952
01:01:37,600 --> 01:01:40,200
I don't know, maybe it's time you did.

953
01:01:42,600 --> 01:01:43,400
What?

954
01:01:46,800 --> 01:01:48,200
Found something to lose.

955
01:01:51,400 --> 01:01:53,000
- Stotzer?
- Yeah?

956
01:01:56,000 --> 01:01:57,400
I'll check on you later.

957
01:02:02,400 --> 01:02:03,200
What is it?

958
01:02:11,400 --> 01:02:12,200
Movement.

959
01:02:13,600 --> 01:02:14,800
What do you see?

960
01:02:19,000 --> 01:02:20,600
Gretchen!

961
01:02:31,800 --> 01:02:35,000
Wait, you're gonna hit Gretchen!

962
01:02:36,600 --> 01:02:37,600
I'm going after her!

963
01:02:37,600 --> 01:02:39,400
- No, John, no!
- Let me go!

964
01:02:39,400 --> 01:02:40,600
- John!
- Let go of me!

965
01:02:40,600 --> 01:02:42,400
- Too late!
- No, not Gretchen!

966
01:02:42,400 --> 01:02:43,800
- She's gone!
- No!

967
01:02:44,800 --> 01:02:46,200
Come on, stop, come on!

968
01:02:54,400 --> 01:02:55,600
I always believed that there had to be

969
01:02:55,600 --> 01:02:59,200
a scientific explanation for everything.

970
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:00,600
Science was the only answer.

971
01:03:02,800 --> 01:03:07,200
Since I've been here I'm
rapidly becoming a skeptic.

972
01:03:13,200 --> 01:03:14,400
Oh, it's the hub.

973
01:03:16,400 --> 01:03:18,000
According to these readings there

974
01:03:18,000 --> 01:03:21,000
haven't been any recent power spikes.

975
01:03:21,000 --> 01:03:22,800
So nobody's using it?

976
01:03:22,800 --> 01:03:24,000
So it would appear.

977
01:03:25,400 --> 01:03:28,400
Well, finally some good news.

978
01:03:29,200 --> 01:03:31,000
That's Gretchen, she's alive!

979
01:03:31,000 --> 01:03:32,600
We don't know what that was.

980
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:33,600
It's her, damn it, Cain!

981
01:03:33,600 --> 01:03:34,600
I know it's her!

982
01:03:34,600 --> 01:03:35,600
John, I know it's awful,

983
01:03:35,600 --> 01:03:37,600
but you can't go out there, alright?

984
01:03:37,600 --> 01:03:39,000
They hunt in packs.

985
01:03:39,000 --> 01:03:41,000
Come on, they communicate,
they lure their prey.

986
01:03:41,000 --> 01:03:43,200
Yeah, we have no idea
where it's coming from, man.

987
01:03:43,200 --> 01:03:44,600
Cain's right, Stotzer.

988
01:03:44,600 --> 01:03:46,000
They could be trying to separate us.

989
01:03:46,000 --> 01:03:48,000
They're bears, damn it!

990
01:03:48,000 --> 01:03:50,400
They could be trying to use her as bait.

991
01:03:50,400 --> 01:03:52,600
John, just relax.

992
01:03:52,600 --> 01:03:54,000
Okay, come on.

993
01:03:55,200 --> 01:03:56,800
Yeah, right, boss.

994
01:04:38,000 --> 01:04:39,000
Gretchen!

995
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:40,800
Oh, my God!

996
01:04:42,000 --> 01:04:43,200
I'm here now.

997
01:04:43,200 --> 01:04:45,600
I'm gonna get you out.

998
01:04:45,600 --> 01:04:47,200
I'm getting you home.

999
01:04:51,800 --> 01:04:52,800
Oh, God, no!

1000
01:04:56,200 --> 01:04:57,000
Gretchen.

1001
01:05:19,800 --> 01:05:22,200
I finished packing
Gretchen's medical supplies.

1002
01:05:24,000 --> 01:05:25,800
I hope we can find the
rest of the hardware.

1003
01:05:25,800 --> 01:05:27,400
As fast as he was moving it's a good bet

1004
01:05:27,400 --> 01:05:28,600
he left a trail we can follow.

1005
01:05:28,600 --> 01:05:30,000
I don't wanna lose anybody else.

1006
01:05:30,000 --> 01:05:32,400
Yeah, we're getting low on ammo.

1007
01:05:32,400 --> 01:05:33,800
Make 'em count.

1008
01:06:31,000 --> 01:06:32,000
Long time, no see.

1009
01:06:35,000 --> 01:06:36,400
Where you headed, Duncan?

1010
01:06:39,200 --> 01:06:40,200
It's not what you think.

1011
01:06:40,200 --> 01:06:42,400
Oh, you didn't leave us for dead?

1012
01:06:42,400 --> 01:06:43,200
No.

1013
01:06:45,800 --> 01:06:47,200
Where's the hub, Duncan?

1014
01:06:47,200 --> 01:06:48,000
It's near.

1015
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:49,800
Let's go.

1016
01:07:17,000 --> 01:07:17,800
My foot!

1017
01:07:19,400 --> 01:07:20,400
Can you move?

1018
01:07:21,800 --> 01:07:23,600
I'm trying, I think it's twisted.

1019
01:07:26,800 --> 01:07:28,200
Use this.

1020
01:07:28,200 --> 01:07:29,600
We're almost to the top.

1021
01:07:29,600 --> 01:07:30,400
Hub's just the other side.

1022
01:07:30,400 --> 01:07:31,600
Let's go!

1023
01:07:31,600 --> 01:07:34,800
Come on, it's not that much further.

1024
01:07:38,400 --> 01:07:39,200
Cain!

1025
01:07:39,200 --> 01:07:41,200
Everybody down!

1026
01:07:48,200 --> 01:07:50,200
Nice shootin', boss.

1027
01:07:53,200 --> 01:07:55,200
We can't afford to stop again, let's go.

1028
01:07:59,200 --> 01:08:00,600
How far are we from the hub?

1029
01:08:01,600 --> 01:08:04,600
I don't know, I haven't
been able to locate it yet.

1030
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:06,800
Why should I trust you?

1031
01:08:06,800 --> 01:08:07,600
Cain!

1032
01:08:07,600 --> 01:08:09,200
Carlson knew that
the planet is unstable.

1033
01:08:09,200 --> 01:08:11,800
The telemetry from the
Unibot confirmed it.

1034
01:08:13,200 --> 01:08:14,000
He set us up!

1035
01:08:18,000 --> 01:08:19,200
What about the oxygen plant?

1036
01:08:19,200 --> 01:08:21,400
It was just a con to get you up here.

1037
01:08:21,400 --> 01:08:23,400
So the planet's worthless?

1038
01:08:23,400 --> 01:08:24,800
That doesn't make any sense.

1039
01:08:25,600 --> 01:08:27,400
No, you're wrong in your assumption

1040
01:08:27,400 --> 01:08:28,800
that this planet is worthless.

1041
01:08:28,800 --> 01:08:30,600
It's got something to do with what

1042
01:08:30,600 --> 01:08:31,400
happened to Harling and his team.

1043
01:08:32,400 --> 01:08:33,800
We found Harling's skull.

1044
01:08:35,800 --> 01:08:36,600
Oh, my God!

1045
01:08:39,600 --> 01:08:40,600
What have I done?

1046
01:08:40,600 --> 01:08:42,200
You can make peace later.

1047
01:08:42,200 --> 01:08:44,400
I need to know exactly
what's going on here.

1048
01:08:47,800 --> 01:08:51,000
Six months ago we sent out a recon party

1049
01:08:51,000 --> 01:08:53,200
of five to do very much what we're doing.

1050
01:08:54,200 --> 01:08:55,600
Explore the planet and establish

1051
01:08:55,600 --> 01:08:57,200
a base for future colonization.

1052
01:08:59,800 --> 01:09:02,200
The first party soon discovered that

1053
01:09:03,200 --> 01:09:06,000
the planet's unstable and
it's developing exponentially.

1054
01:09:07,600 --> 01:09:09,000
It will eventually implode.

1055
01:09:10,800 --> 01:09:13,800
The genetically mutated bears
are much smarter and stronger

1056
01:09:13,800 --> 01:09:15,800
than anything we've ever seen on Earth.

1057
01:09:15,800 --> 01:09:16,600
Then, why?

1058
01:09:17,600 --> 01:09:19,800
If the planet can't be colonized,

1059
01:09:19,800 --> 01:09:22,400
then why come back here at all?

1060
01:09:22,400 --> 01:09:24,800
Because first team
discovered something else.

1061
01:09:25,600 --> 01:09:28,200
Something that makes it
unnecessary to leave the Earth!

1062
01:09:28,200 --> 01:09:29,800
What is it?

1063
01:09:29,800 --> 01:09:32,200
The team had missed three check-ins.

1064
01:09:32,200 --> 01:09:33,600
Fortunately, one of them
survived long enough

1065
01:09:33,600 --> 01:09:35,400
to program the Unibot to return.

1066
01:10:27,200 --> 01:10:29,400
It wasn't like
anything we'd ever seen.

1067
01:10:29,400 --> 01:10:32,400
Cellular regeneration
on a macro time scale.

1068
01:10:34,400 --> 01:10:36,200
What the?

1069
01:10:55,600 --> 01:10:59,400
Carlson calls it 'vida
sera', the serum of life.

1070
01:10:59,400 --> 01:11:01,400
So is that why he came here, to find it?

1071
01:11:01,400 --> 01:11:03,000
With a perfect sample of vida sera

1072
01:11:03,000 --> 01:11:04,800
we can replicate it back on Earth.

1073
01:11:05,800 --> 01:11:06,600
Can you imagine?

1074
01:11:07,600 --> 01:11:09,600
A vaccine capable of rejuvenating cells

1075
01:11:09,600 --> 01:11:11,400
that have been ravaged by cancer!

1076
01:11:11,400 --> 01:11:13,400
Lung cells that have been
damaged by pollution!

1077
01:11:13,400 --> 01:11:17,400
Mankind can evolve and live
on Earth as polluted as it is.

1078
01:11:17,400 --> 01:11:18,200
Let's roll!

1079
01:11:18,200 --> 01:11:20,600
Why not just send a bot
to collect the sample?

1080
01:11:20,600 --> 01:11:21,800
Why put us at risk?

1081
01:11:21,800 --> 01:11:23,600
Because we didn't have exact coordinates

1082
01:11:23,600 --> 01:11:25,600
and remote surface scans
came back negative.

1083
01:11:25,600 --> 01:11:27,000
Well, you should have told us.

1084
01:11:27,000 --> 01:11:28,000
You could have at least--

1085
01:11:28,000 --> 01:11:29,000
Carlson swore me to silence.

1086
01:11:29,000 --> 01:11:30,400
He said he'd make me responsible

1087
01:11:30,400 --> 01:11:33,000
for the disappearance of the first team!

1088
01:11:33,000 --> 01:11:35,600
And he gave you a share of the profits.

1089
01:11:35,600 --> 01:11:37,200
I didn't think I had a choice.

1090
01:11:38,800 --> 01:11:40,200
You still monitoring that hub?

1091
01:11:40,200 --> 01:11:41,800
Yeah.

1092
01:11:41,800 --> 01:11:44,200
Less than a kilometer to go, that way.

1093
01:11:44,200 --> 01:11:45,200
Yeah, we're going home.

1094
01:11:45,200 --> 01:11:46,400
Wait a minute, wait a minute!

1095
01:11:46,400 --> 01:11:47,400
What about the vida sera?

1096
01:11:47,400 --> 01:11:48,200
We've come this far!

1097
01:11:48,200 --> 01:11:49,800
It's Carlson's problem, it's not ours.

1098
01:11:49,800 --> 01:11:51,600
Think about what it
can do for the Earth.

1099
01:11:51,600 --> 01:11:52,400
For the evolution of man!

1100
01:11:52,400 --> 01:11:54,200
Cain, Duncan is right.

1101
01:11:54,200 --> 01:11:56,800
This may be our only chance
to get ahold of this stuff.

1102
01:11:56,800 --> 01:11:58,600
We can't really afford to pass that up.

1103
01:11:58,600 --> 01:11:59,400
My job is to protect your ass

1104
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:00,600
and get us out of here in one piece,

1105
01:12:00,600 --> 01:12:02,000
and that's what I'm gonna do.

1106
01:12:08,400 --> 01:12:10,600
The missing cases.

1107
01:12:10,600 --> 01:12:11,800
I told you I sent them!

1108
01:12:11,800 --> 01:12:13,400
Alright, let's check them out.

1109
01:12:25,600 --> 01:12:26,400
They're empty!

1110
01:12:27,600 --> 01:12:31,000
Carlson!

1111
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:32,600
It's empty.

1112
01:12:43,400 --> 01:12:44,600
Hey guys, over here!

1113
01:12:53,200 --> 01:12:55,000
Without the hub we're stuck here.

1114
01:12:56,000 --> 01:12:58,000
Where the hell is Carlson?

1115
01:12:58,000 --> 01:12:59,600
I don't know.

1116
01:12:59,600 --> 01:13:02,000
I swear guys, I'm a victim, too!

1117
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:03,200
Well, we gotta find him.

1118
01:13:03,200 --> 01:13:05,000
He's gotta be around here somewhere.

1119
01:13:05,000 --> 01:13:06,800
I bet the vida sera's nearby.

1120
01:13:10,800 --> 01:13:11,800
Cain!

1121
01:13:11,800 --> 01:13:13,600
No, wait, don't go over there!

1122
01:13:13,600 --> 01:13:15,000
No, no, come on.

1123
01:13:15,000 --> 01:13:16,000
What, come on!

1124
01:13:21,200 --> 01:13:22,600
Shoot me!

1125
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:26,400
Shoot me!

1126
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:49,000
We gotta get out of here.

1127
01:13:49,000 --> 01:13:51,000
They're gonna pick us
off one by one, let's go.

1128
01:14:21,200 --> 01:14:22,200
There it is!

1129
01:14:30,600 --> 01:14:31,800
Come on, shoot it!

1130
01:14:31,800 --> 01:14:33,800
It's too close to the hub.

1131
01:14:38,000 --> 01:14:38,800
Hold this.

1132
01:14:40,200 --> 01:14:42,000
What are you doing?

1133
01:14:42,000 --> 01:14:45,200
I'm gonna run a distraction
while you two fix the hub.

1134
01:14:45,200 --> 01:14:47,200
- What?
- That's suicide!

1135
01:15:00,000 --> 01:15:01,800
This is insane.

1136
01:15:06,200 --> 01:15:07,200
Come here.

1137
01:15:08,400 --> 01:15:09,200
Come on.

1138
01:15:18,000 --> 01:15:19,000
Let's go!

1139
01:15:32,000 --> 01:15:32,800
Come on!

1140
01:15:39,400 --> 01:15:40,400
Okay.

1141
01:15:41,600 --> 01:15:42,400
That's it.

1142
01:15:46,400 --> 01:15:47,800
Okay, okay, okay.

1143
01:15:55,200 --> 01:15:56,600
The circuit board's gone!

1144
01:16:54,800 --> 01:16:55,800
Pot roast.

1145
01:17:05,000 --> 01:17:06,400
Allison!

1146
01:17:11,200 --> 01:17:12,400
You bastard!

1147
01:17:14,600 --> 01:17:16,400
Didn't think you'd last this long.

1148
01:17:18,000 --> 01:17:21,800
By now, I should learn not
to underestimate my Allison.

1149
01:17:24,200 --> 01:17:25,800
I think you've done enough damage.

1150
01:17:28,400 --> 01:17:30,000
She got to you, you fool.

1151
01:17:31,400 --> 01:17:33,400
You know how rich you can be?

1152
01:17:33,400 --> 01:17:35,800
Yeah, maybe, but I'm learning

1153
01:17:35,800 --> 01:17:38,600
that there's more to
life than money, James.

1154
01:17:38,600 --> 01:17:40,200
Who taught you that, Cain?

1155
01:17:44,000 --> 01:17:45,600
Where is he?

1156
01:17:45,600 --> 01:17:47,800
He died protecting us.

1157
01:17:47,800 --> 01:17:49,400
Unlike you, he was concerned about

1158
01:17:49,400 --> 01:17:51,000
what happened to the rest of us.

1159
01:17:52,400 --> 01:17:54,400
You're making a mistake.

1160
01:17:54,400 --> 01:17:55,200
No, I already made one.

1161
01:17:55,200 --> 01:17:56,400
Now, you shut it!

1162
01:17:57,400 --> 01:17:58,400
It's your fortune.

1163
01:17:59,400 --> 01:18:01,200
Will you hold this?

1164
01:18:02,600 --> 01:18:07,600
The lady said shut up!

1165
01:18:11,600 --> 01:18:12,800
I got it.

1166
01:18:12,800 --> 01:18:16,000
I suppose he's told you he's
innocent of all this, huh?

1167
01:18:16,000 --> 01:18:16,800
Duncan!

1168
01:18:19,600 --> 01:18:21,400
He should have the circuit board.

1169
01:18:21,400 --> 01:18:22,400
Cain!

1170
01:18:24,800 --> 01:18:25,600
Oh, my God!

1171
01:18:25,600 --> 01:18:27,400
How long's it gonna take
to get it up and running?

1172
01:18:28,400 --> 01:18:29,800
It's done.

1173
01:18:29,800 --> 01:18:30,800
Get on it.

1174
01:18:38,200 --> 01:18:39,400
So, is that it?

1175
01:18:39,400 --> 01:18:42,200
The vida sera, it was
so important to you.

1176
01:18:43,400 --> 01:18:45,800
You risked all our lives and for what?

1177
01:18:45,800 --> 01:18:48,000
So you could be even richer?

1178
01:18:48,000 --> 01:18:49,800
What else is there?

1179
01:18:50,800 --> 01:18:53,400
Something you don't know
anything about; humanity.

1180
01:18:56,200 --> 01:18:58,400
You'll all pay for
this when we get back.

1181
01:18:59,600 --> 01:19:01,600
No, no, no, you'll pay.

1182
01:19:01,600 --> 01:19:03,200
I'll be filing for divorce.

1183
01:19:08,800 --> 01:19:10,200
It's not working.

1184
01:19:10,200 --> 01:19:11,400
He's done something to the circuitry.

1185
01:19:11,400 --> 01:19:13,400
We need the motherboard.

1186
01:19:20,200 --> 01:19:21,800
We're running out of time.

1187
01:19:21,800 --> 01:19:24,600
The core tectonics are shifting again.

1188
01:19:24,600 --> 01:19:26,600
This whole place is going to erupt.

1189
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:30,600
Where is it?

1190
01:19:33,600 --> 01:19:34,400
Cain.

1191
01:19:38,800 --> 01:19:40,000
I got two shells left.

1192
01:19:41,800 --> 01:19:43,200
Get it out of him.

1193
01:19:45,000 --> 01:19:48,000
Point it at him and pull the trigger.

1194
01:19:56,600 --> 01:19:58,400
Get it out of him.

1195
01:20:07,200 --> 01:20:08,000
Where is it?

1196
01:20:10,200 --> 01:20:12,000
You're not gonna kill me.

1197
01:20:23,000 --> 01:20:24,000
I'll blow it off.

1198
01:20:28,000 --> 01:20:28,800
Where is it?

1199
01:20:30,000 --> 01:20:31,600
My pack.

1200
01:20:31,600 --> 01:20:32,600
In the cave.

1201
01:20:34,600 --> 01:20:35,800
I think it's a trick.

1202
01:20:39,000 --> 01:20:39,800
I'll go.

1203
01:20:41,400 --> 01:20:42,600
Caves go on forever.

1204
01:20:44,000 --> 01:20:45,600
You need me to find it.

1205
01:20:45,600 --> 01:20:47,000
I'll risk it.

1206
01:20:47,000 --> 01:20:48,400
Let me go.

1207
01:20:48,400 --> 01:20:50,600
- No, no.
- Cain, let me go.

1208
01:20:51,600 --> 01:20:52,400
A deal?

1209
01:20:54,400 --> 01:20:56,400
I'll take you to the motherboard

1210
01:20:56,400 --> 01:20:57,600
if you don't say anything about

1211
01:20:57,600 --> 01:20:59,800
what happened here when
we get back to Earth.

1212
01:21:01,600 --> 01:21:02,800
We all go.

1213
01:21:02,800 --> 01:21:03,800
You lead.

1214
01:21:04,600 --> 01:21:05,400
Get up.

1215
01:21:06,800 --> 01:21:08,800
Come on, get up, get up.

1216
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:12,200
What would we have done if you'd died?

1217
01:21:12,200 --> 01:21:14,200
And why would you give Duncan the gun?

1218
01:21:16,000 --> 01:21:18,000
You're full of surprises.

1219
01:21:32,600 --> 01:21:34,600
Alright, which way?

1220
01:21:34,600 --> 01:21:37,000
Left, it's not far.

1221
01:21:37,000 --> 01:21:38,600
It stinks in here.

1222
01:21:46,000 --> 01:21:46,800
You okay?

1223
01:21:49,600 --> 01:21:51,400
Yeah.

1224
01:21:51,400 --> 01:21:53,200
- You alright?
- Yeah.

1225
01:22:58,200 --> 01:23:01,200
Cain, I don't think this is a rock.

1226
01:23:35,400 --> 01:23:36,200
Duncan!

1227
01:24:06,200 --> 01:24:08,800
Cain, hold them off!

1228
01:24:10,400 --> 01:24:12,200
Allison, get out of here!

1229
01:24:12,200 --> 01:24:13,600
I'm not going without you!

1230
01:24:13,600 --> 01:24:15,600
It can only take one at a time, go!

1231
01:24:21,600 --> 01:24:23,600
I'm right behind you, go!

1232
01:24:28,200 --> 01:24:29,000
Allison!

1233
01:25:40,400 --> 01:25:42,600
Thank you all for coming.

1234
01:25:46,000 --> 01:25:50,600
As the sole inheritor of
the Calron Corporation

1235
01:25:50,600 --> 01:25:53,800
my late husband, James Carlson,

1236
01:25:53,800 --> 01:25:55,600
has left me a legacy of healing.

1237
01:25:56,600 --> 01:25:58,800
And it is with great pride that

1238
01:25:58,800 --> 01:26:02,600
I announce to you our newest product;

1239
01:26:02,600 --> 01:26:07,200
a cellular regeneration
compound, Vida Sera.

1240
01:26:08,800 --> 01:26:10,000
The miraculous properties of

1241
01:26:10,000 --> 01:26:13,000
this compound are already being explored.

1242
01:26:13,000 --> 01:26:16,800
Regrowth of cells damaged
by cancer and disease.

1243
01:26:16,800 --> 01:26:19,400
Even regrowth of entire limbs.

1244
01:26:20,600 --> 01:26:22,600
And I am pleased to introduce to you

1245
01:26:22,600 --> 01:26:27,200
our first successful test
subject; Randall Cain.

1246
01:26:35,600 --> 01:26:39,000
We've barely scratched the
surface of the serum's potential.

1247
01:26:39,000 --> 01:26:42,600
And I pledge to you
now that I will utilize

1248
01:26:42,600 --> 01:26:45,200
the full assets of Calron Corporation

1249
01:26:45,200 --> 01:26:47,000
and its subsidiaries to ensure

1250
01:26:47,000 --> 01:26:50,000
that every man, woman and child on Earth

1251
01:26:50,000 --> 01:26:54,200
is given a new chance at
a full and healthy life.

1252
01:26:55,800 --> 01:26:57,600
May each of us make the most of it.

1253
01:27:01,400 --> 01:27:03,000
This way, please!

1254
01:27:03,000 --> 01:27:04,800
This way, please!

1255
01:27:04,800 --> 01:27:06,000
This way!

